EXPRESS [ISO 911 is an information modeling language being developed to describe the information content of the international standard informally called STEP lWilson 87,89,90] [Chan 901, itself designed for the exchange of product definition data among computer applications for manufacturing. An entity consists of a set of attributes of basic, user-defined or entity types. In addition, an entity type can be defined as a subtype of another entity type (the supertype), in which case it inherits all the attributes of the supertype. Constraints can be placed on the values of attributes, and rules can be specified to relate the values of attributes within or across entities. For example, a point on a curve can be defined as: